FBIS3-7922 "dreeu041aa_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 March 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Silajdzic, Granic, Zubak Comment AU0203113694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1100 GMT 2 Mar 94 AU0203113694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Statements by Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic, Croatian Foreign Minister Mate Granic, and Kresimir Zubak, representative of the Bosnian Croats, in Washington on 2 March; Silajdzic, Granic, Zubak speak in English with superimposed Serbo-Croatian translation -- recorded] [Text] [Silajdzic] We hope and pray that this is the first step toward peace. [Granic] Today we have taken a great step forward. The U.S. Administration has contributed immensely to achieving a final agreement. [Zubak] I am convinced that today we have taken the first step toward establishing peace and protecting human lives in Bosnia-Herzegovina.
